[If any reader can explain why fermented urine should have any effect
on this disease, we would like to hear from him or her. Since ProMED
currently lacks a plant moderator, I reproduce here a comment by a
previous one. - Mod.JW.
"[There is confusion in the nomenclature because the same name is
being applied to 3 different diseases. 2 pathogens have been
identified: the bacterium, _Xanthomonas campestris_ pv. _musacearum_
(Xpm), and the fungus _Fusarium oxysporum_ f. sp. _cubense_ (Foc),
which is frequently seen in Uganda and is prevalent in other African
countries. The third disease is matooke disorder, the etiology of
which remains unknown [matooke is a cooking banana & a staple food in
Uganda - Mod.JW]. This report is not unexpected given the
distribution of diseased banana plants in Uganda.
There are 2 names in use for the wilt disease caused by Foc; Fusarium
wilt & Panama disease. The disease was first reported in Australia in
1876 and has since been reported in all banana-producing regions
except islands in the South Pacific, the Mediterranean, Melanesia,
and Somalia. There are 4 races of Foc, 3 of which are banana
pathogens. An excellent account of the disease can be found at the
following URL:
<http://www.planthealthprogress.org/current/management/banana> - Mod.DH"]
[There is a fusarium wilt disease fact sheet with photographs at
<http://www.banana.go.ug/downloads/fusarium_fact_sheet.pdf>, - CopyEd MJ]
